WEBVTT

00:01.102 --> 00:01.235
.

00:06.474 --> 00:07.408
male narrator:
In the criminal justice system,

00:09.710 --> 00:12.180
sexually based offenses are
considered especially heinous.

00:12.180 --> 00:14.548
In New York City,
the dedicated detectives

00:14.548 --> 00:16.384
who investigate
these vicious felonies

00:16.384 --> 00:17.851
are members
of an elite squad

00:17.851 --> 00:19.853
known
as the Special Victims Unit.

00:19.853 --> 00:21.589
These are their stories.

00:21.589 --> 00:22.856
[dramatic notes]

00:22.856 --> 00:23.924
- Another push-in rape?

00:23.924 --> 00:25.226
- Looks like it,
Lieutenant.

00:25.226 --> 00:26.394
Guy follows the wife

00:26.394 --> 00:27.761
into her apartment
around 11:00

00:27.761 --> 00:29.363
intending
to rape her.

00:29.363 --> 00:32.066
Husband comes home,
gets pistol-whipped.

00:32.066 --> 00:34.102
- Just like the one
on Frederick Douglass.

00:34.102 --> 00:37.105
- Worse.
He stayed longer this time.

00:37.105 --> 00:39.273
We got the call
a little after 6:00 a.m.

00:39.273 --> 00:40.908
Suspect left them
tied up.

00:40.908 --> 00:44.245
Wife used voice-activated Siri
to call 911.

00:44.245 --> 00:46.013
- Good for her.
- Uh-huh.

00:46.013 --> 00:47.448
- So she's still
conscious?

00:47.448 --> 00:49.317
- They're working on her.

00:50.551 --> 00:53.020
- Doom, Campesi,
twice in two weeks.

00:53.020 --> 00:54.688
- Long, hot summer.

00:54.688 --> 00:56.790
They're working on the wife,
Cynthia Harris, in there.

00:56.790 --> 00:58.025
- She give
a description?

00:58.025 --> 00:59.560
- Not yet.
EMTs are just finishing.

00:59.560 --> 01:02.796
- Mrs. Harris?
Hi, I'm Lieutenant Benson.

01:02.796 --> 01:04.198
Can you tell me anything
about the man

01:04.198 --> 01:06.200
who did this to you?

01:06.200 --> 01:11.172
- He was, um, black,
tall.

01:11.172 --> 01:12.973
Hold on.

01:12.973 --> 01:14.975
My daughter.
Oh, my God.

01:14.975 --> 01:15.976
Do you have my daughter?

01:15.976 --> 01:17.445
- Your daughter?

01:17.445 --> 01:19.347
- Sophie, she was at
a sleepover down the hall.

01:19.347 --> 01:20.681
She got homesick
and she came home early.

01:20.681 --> 01:22.150
I think he took her.

01:22.150 --> 01:23.717
- A sleepover?
How old is your daughter?

01:23.717 --> 01:25.153
- She's 12.
- Okay,

01:25.153 --> 01:26.787
let's get her out of here, guys.
- [sobs]

01:26.787 --> 01:28.889
- We're gonna find her.
We're gonna find her.

01:28.889 --> 01:31.359
- No videos.
No witnesses so far.

01:31.359 --> 01:33.994
- All right, he took
their 12-year-old daughter.

01:33.994 --> 01:35.829
Probably didn't want to be seen
dragging her out

01:35.829 --> 01:37.698
in broad daylight, so let's
lock the building down now.

01:37.698 --> 01:39.167
- On it.

01:47.841 --> 01:49.977
- Clear down here.

01:49.977 --> 01:51.979
[police radio chatter]

01:51.979 --> 01:55.015
[siren wailing]

02:04.192 --> 02:07.195
- Roof's clear.

02:14.935 --> 02:17.305
- Anything?

02:17.305 --> 02:19.207
Storage room is clear.

02:27.215 --> 02:28.482
- Clear in the hallway.

02:30.518 --> 02:33.287
- Check over there.
- Right away.

02:33.287 --> 02:34.355
- Clear here.

02:34.355 --> 02:37.391
- Clear!

02:40.694 --> 02:41.962
- Hey!

02:41.962 --> 02:44.031
Hey, I found her!
Call a bus!

02:44.031 --> 02:45.599
Sophie,
are you okay?

02:45.599 --> 02:47.034
Are you all right?
Come on.

02:47.034 --> 02:49.002
Come on.
I got you, come on.

02:49.002 --> 02:52.306
Come on, I got you.
Got you.

02:52.306 --> 02:54.342
Hey!
I need a gurney over here!

02:54.342 --> 02:57.245
Come on!
Come on.

02:57.245 --> 02:59.680
- Here you go.
We got you, Sophie, we got you.

02:59.680 --> 03:01.249
- Where's my mommy
and my daddy?

03:01.249 --> 03:02.750
- They're okay.
They're okay.

03:02.750 --> 03:04.552
You're gonna be fine,
Sophie.

03:04.552 --> 03:07.355
All right,
I'll ride with her.

03:07.355 --> 03:10.391
Find this guy.
Ready?

03:12.560 --> 03:15.563
[dramatic music]

03:59.340 --> 03:59.473
